com.oracle.truffle.api.interop

Class ForeignAccess

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.oracle.truffle.api.interop.ForeignAccess

  • public final class ForeignAccess
extends Object
    Encapsulates types of access to TruffleObject. If you want to expose your own objects to foreign language implementations, you need to implement TruffleObject and its TruffleObject.getForeignAccess() method. To create instance of ForeignAccess , use one of the factory methods available in this class.
    Since:
    0.8 or earlier

      • sendKeyInfo

        public static int sendKeyInfo(Node keyInfoNode,
                              TruffleObject receiver,
                              Object identifier)
        Sends a KEY_INFO message to the foreign receiver object by executing the keyInfoNode. If the object does not support the message, the presence of the key is found by iteration over it's keys on a slow path and a default info is returned.
        Parameters:
        keyInfoNode - the createNode created by Message.createNode()
        receiver - foreign object to receive the message passed to Message.createNode() method
        identifier - name of the property to get the info of.
        Returns:
        an integer value with bit flags described at KeyInfo.
        Throws:
        ClassCastException - if the createNode has not been created by Message.createNode() method.
        Since:
        0.26

      • sendKeys

        public static TruffleObject sendKeys(Node keysNode,
                                     TruffleObject receiver)
                              throws UnsupportedMessageException
        Sends a Message.KEYS message to the foreign receiver object.
        Parameters:
        keysNode - the createNode created by Message.createNode()
        receiver - foreign object to receive the message passed to Message.createNode() method
        Returns:
        return an instance of TruffleObject that responds to Message.HAS_SIZE and Message.GET_SIZE and its 0 to size - 1 indexes contain String names of the properties of the receiver object
        Throws:
        UnsupportedMessageException - if the message isn't handled
        ClassCastException - if the createNode has not been created by Message.createNode() method.
        Since:
        0.24

      • sendKeys

        public static TruffleObject sendKeys(Node keysNode,
                                     TruffleObject receiver,
                                     boolean includeInternal)
                              throws UnsupportedMessageException
        Sends a Message.KEYS message to the foreign receiver object, with a specification of whether internal keys should be included in the result, or not.
        Parameters:
        keysNode - the createNode created by Message.createNode()
        receiver - foreign object to receive the message passed to Message.createNode() method
        includeInternal - true to include internal keys in the result, false to abandon them.
        Returns:
        return an instance of TruffleObject that responds to Message.HAS_SIZE and Message.GET_SIZE and its 0 to size - 1 indexes contain String names of the properties of the receiver object
        Throws:
        UnsupportedMessageException - if the message isn't handled
        ClassCastException - if the createNode has not been created by Message.createNode() method.
        Since:
        0.26
